  <bioghist id="aspace_04e20c05d1151a36e13a55e29d34a8d6">
    <head>Biography/History</head>
<p>James M. Klain earned his Bachelor of Arts in Drama at UCLA in 1943, and although he did not obtain further degrees, continued his studies there in Theater Arts and Education. Klain went on to work at UCLA as the director of the Campus Activities Service Office, directed the renovation of Royce Hall (1982-1984), served as stage manager at such venues as the Royce Hall Auditorium and Pauley Pavilion (1947-), and held positions as charter member and Vice President of the Theater, Film and Television Alumni Association.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_b910170af82a06b8803d8f4c1c61f760">
    <head>Scope and Content</head>
<p>Record Series 616 contains photographic images of Royce Hall at the University of California, Los Angeles, taken and assembled by James M. Klain. Files include color and black and white photographs, slides, color transparencies, proofs, and negatives of Royce Hall images. Additionally, this collection features collected images of Royce Hall in print, photographs of other locations on the UCLA campus, and photographs of the Watts Towers in Los Angeles, California.</p><p>This is an inactive record series; no additional University records are expected to be added.</p>  </scopecontent>
